[thinking] **Evaluating testing tools**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm noticing that the generated scaffold includes an assertion library but lacks an actor testkit. This leaves room for an agent to create ad-hoc CountDownLatch actors or use ask patterns. On the other hand, Pekko TestKit serves as the standard test companion module for asserting messages and managing watchers. This could lead to inconsistencies, so I'm curious about how to best approach testing in this setup. Let’s explore the options further!
[thinking] 
[thinking] **Updating test practices**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I think we need to phrase our approach carefully. We don’t need environment or system properties when updating tests. It’s essential to avoid using the 1.x removed TypedActor and TypedProps. Instead, we should focus on the classic ActorSystem and Props alongside serialization APIs. Also, it’s crucial to always terminate ActorSystems after tests. This could be helpful to keep in mind, but it doesn’t necessarily require a whole setup.
[thinking] 
