alization APIs. Also, it’s crucial to always terminate ActorSystems after tests. This could be helpful to keep in mind, but it doesn’t necessarily require a whole setup.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra dependency, Docker image, environment variable, or system property is required for meaningful coverage of org.apache.pekko:pekko-actor_2.13:2.0.0-M1. The resolved artifact only depends on scala-library 2.13.18 and com.typesafe:config 1.4.5, and classic actor APIs such as ActorSystem and Props remain in the target artifact. The observed failure is caused by existing tests using removed 1.x deprecated TypedActor/TypedProps APIs, not by missing setup.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Update tests away from removed org.apache.pekko.actor.TypedActor/TypedProps APIs in Pekko 2.0.0-M1. Prefer classic actor coverage that stays within pekko-actor_2.13, such as ActorSystem creation, Props, actor lifecycle/message handling, serializers, dispatchers/config, and orderly ActorSystem termination.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Pekko 2.0.0-M1 is a milestone release with many deprecated APIs removed, so generated tests may need API refresh rather than setup.\",\n    \"Adding pekko-actor-typed_2.13 would cover a separate typed actor module and would not restore the removed org.apache.pekko.actor.TypedActor APIs from pekko-actor_2.13 1.x.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_066fbe25bef37181016a422fd4ad4081958fe7d48acb22b0fd\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2158, "output": 1341, "cacheRead": 38400, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 41899, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782722494003, "responseId": "resp_066fbe25bef37181016a422fbea2608195ab6fb57a2996f559"}}
